This is a codebase for an android app running a device I built for teaching how to play piano, which is shown at the youtube video 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YC_lJPqYajg

The work was presented at North Carolina State University's Maker Faire. It was covered by the school's newspaper.  

https://www.technicianonline.com/news/maker-faire-event-showcases-creativity-n-c-innovation/article_cfa9f4b0-f1dc-11e3-9679-001a4bcf6878.html

Since 2014, the photo from my exihibit has been used as the cover photo for the main landing page of NCSU Engineering's Outreach office. 

https://www.engr.ncsu.edu/outreach/

The code for the android app driving the device is in the content. 

Sorry my app's name is 'l'. I am lazy like this. Also there is no explanation on each part of the app source code. email me at kisurb@gmail.com for questions. I will do my best to answer. 
